GPLv3 is a poor fit for the type of material in our factory data. There are a lot of difficult questions that arise, like, is a modified factory patch a derivative work? If a factory patch is included in your DAW project files, is your DAW project now GPLv3? etc

Considering many patches will be culled anyway in XT2.0, this presents a good opportunity to re-license this data (with the permission of all IP owners) to a license that is designed for something other than code, that clarifies matters like these.

@baconpaul has suggested [CC-BY-SA 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/).
